snp3.12:2.3:
“Those who do not understand suffering,
or the origin of suffering;
who do not know where suffering
completely ceases without remainder;
and who do not know the path
that leads to the allaying of suffering: (1)

snp3.12:6.5:
“Existence is conditioned by clinging;
an existent being undergoes suffering.
For one who is born there is death;
this is the origin of suffering. (19)

snp3.12:7.5:
“A bhikkhu with a peaceful mind,
who has cut off the craving for existence,
has finished with the wandering on in births;
for him there is no renewed existence. (23)
